Making a few language mistakes while learning on busuu Getting some grammar confused Forgot what a word means Don t worry it s completely natural. After all if you don t make mistakes then you re not learning. We ve now made it easier to focus on your weaker areas you no longer need to repeat an entire activity just to correct a few mistakes. Instead you ll find those exercises repeat themselves so you get another try. This way you ll benefit from your mistakes! Practice makes perfect!

It s finally here a new look for busuu! Over the past month we ve been working on something very special: an all new look for our courses! We ve listened to your suggestions added some cool ideas of our own and poured it all into what could be the biggest update in busuu history. Why did we do it We wanted to make your learning experience even better by improving one of the core parts of our app: the Learn tab. We ve now given you the ability to jump straight into where you left off by pressing on the Next up button. It s now even easier to track your progress by being able to clearly see your overall progress through each lesson. And we ve polished it all off with stunning imagery and some rather fancy animations.

Learning a language is all about speaking it right Guess what You can finally improve both your written and spoken conversational skills with native speakers from all over the world Because we believe language is about conversation busuu is the first language learning app in the world to offer spoken conversations with native speakers. With this new exercise type we ve added voice to our tremendously popular writing exercises now renamed Conversations . Members of our wonderful community will then give you feedback on your exercise by talking or writing back. You can have whole conversations within threads of written and spoken replies. We can t wait to hear you speak!

We all love connecting with other language learners and practicing with them. That s what makes busuu so special! After all the improvements we ve recently released to our community features new cards layout replies and Best Correction it was time to finally launch what many of you have asked...Friends! You can now friend other busuu learners you ve interacted with keep in touch with them and learn together. Send your Writing exercises to your friends for correction or have a look in the Friends feed in Help Others to see what the Writing exercises they have submitted. Get and give back! You can now add other busuu learners as friends from their profile by tapping on Add friend . Once your request is accepted you can see your friends writing exercises in the Friends tab and send correction requests. After you ve submitted a Writing exercise you can choose up to 5 friends to send it to and they will be notified. You can also see the Writing exercises they have submitted in the Friends feed in Help Others so you re always able to help them. Finally we ve added a Notification Center so you can keep track of all your interactions with our wonderful community.

You can now add other busuu learners as friends from their profile by tapping on Add friend . Once your request is accepted you can see your friends writing exercises in the Friends tab and send correction requests. After you ve submitted a Writing exercise you can choose up to 5 friends to send it to and they will be notified. You can also see the Writing exercises they have submitted in the Friends feed in Help Others so you re always able to help them. Finally we ve added a Notification Center so you can keep track of all your interactions with our wonderful community.

We have massively improved My Vocabulary so you can now see the strength of each word and practice weak ones. See that little health bar on each word It represents the strength level of the word figured out by our algorithm. Every time you review a word using our Vocabulary Trainer its strength level will increase. Simply tap the button at the bottom of the screen and choose which set of words you d like to train. Why not all of them Or just your favourites Or maybe your weak words only If you enjoy busuu please leave a nice review on the store.

Major update! You can now save any word or sentence you encounter through the course for fast and on the go access. The list of words you have saved is then stored in a vocabulary bank My Vocabulary where you can access the details of your saved words: translations key phrases pictures sounds and translations. We have also released a companion Apple Watch app to enable you to access your saved vocabulary anytime and from your wrist. All the vocabulary saved on the iPhone app is immediately synchronised with your Apple Watch and you can also access translations key phrases and pictures. Learning on the go has never been easier!
